1
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,366
[MAN]
I'LL GET YOU.

2
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:14,333
TODAY'S THE DAY I'M GONNA--
[GASPS]

3
00:00:19,566 --> 00:00:21,400
THERE YOU ARE, YOU DEMON.

4
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:24,900
I'M READY FOR YOU.
I'M GONNA...

5
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:28,066
TAKE YOUR FISHY ASS DOWN!

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,566
♪ [MAN SINGING
IN JAPANESE]

7
00:02:03,824 --> 00:02:06,858
[RIN]
SUMMERTIME!
THE OCEAN!

8
00:02:06,891 --> 00:02:08,424
[SHIMA]
THE BIKINIS!

9
00:02:08,458 --> 00:02:11,622
LET'S HIT ON CHICKS!
TIME TO HIT THE WATER,
OKUMURA.

10
00:02:11,655 --> 00:02:13,288
COME ON, IZUMO,
GET CHANGED.

11
00:02:13,322 --> 00:02:14,655
SWIMSUITS, PEOPLE.
HURRY. CHOP, CHOP.

12
00:02:14,688 --> 00:02:19,688
OH, MAN, I LOVE THE OCEAN!

13
00:02:23,488 --> 00:02:25,222
MAN, THIS SUCKS.

14
00:02:25,255 --> 00:02:26,788
[WHINES]

15
00:02:26,822 --> 00:02:28,722
NOT NOW.
I SWEAR THE WATER'S--

16
00:02:28,755 --> 00:02:31,888
GO FIGURE.
WE GET STUCK FLIPPING SQUIDS
AT THE SHOP ALL DAY...

17
00:02:31,922 --> 00:02:34,722
WITH ALL THESE
VOLUPTUOUS BABES AROUND.

18
00:02:34,755 --> 00:02:37,188
STEP ON UP, FOLKS,
WE'RE GONNA ROCK YOUR STOMACHS.

19
00:02:37,222 --> 00:02:40,922
OUR GRILLED SQUID IS SO AWESOME
IT MELTS IN YOUR MOUTH.

20
00:02:40,955 --> 00:02:43,488
YOU WON'T MIND SELLING
YOUR SOUL FOR A TASTE.

21
00:02:43,522 --> 00:02:46,588
IN THE FACE OF TRAGEDY,
YOU'RE BEING A GOOD SPORT.

22
00:02:46,622 --> 00:02:50,955
HUH? OH, WELL.
I DON'T MIND DOING
STUFF LIKE THIS.

23
00:02:50,988 --> 00:02:52,455
THE THING IS--

24
00:02:52,488 --> 00:02:55,288
[SHIMA]
THE THING IS
WE'RE LACKING CUSTOMERS.

25
00:02:55,322 --> 00:02:58,055
MAN, I DON'T GET
WHAT WE'RE DOING WRONG.

26
00:02:58,088 --> 00:03:00,188
THE SQUID LOOKS DAMN GOOD.

27
00:03:00,222 --> 00:03:01,688
[KURO]
THEY SURE SMELL TASTY.

28
00:03:01,722 --> 00:03:04,622
RIN, CAN I HAVE ONE,
PLEASE?

29
00:03:04,655 --> 00:03:06,455
THEY'RE FOR SALE.
SORRY, PAL.

30
00:03:06,488 --> 00:03:08,455
HEY, IS THAT HIM?

31
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:11,855
THAT'S YOUR NEW FAMILIAR,
THE CAT SI, ISN'T IT?

32
00:03:11,888 --> 00:03:14,588
YEAH. I FIGURED I'D BRING HIM
'CAUSE THEY SAID
IT WAS A MISSION.

33
00:03:14,622 --> 00:03:16,922
HA. MISSION, MY ASS.
THEY SAY WE'RE HERE...

34
00:03:16,955 --> 00:03:19,355
TO COLLECT SEAWEED
FOR DEMON-WARDING POTIONS.

35
00:03:19,388 --> 00:03:22,588
CRAP. THEY GOT US
WORKING RETAIL, MAN.

36
00:03:22,622 --> 00:03:25,988
DID YOU KNOW THIS SNACK BAR
AND THE PLACE WE'RE STAYING AT,

37
00:03:26,022 --> 00:03:29,255
BOTH OF THEM BELONG
TO OLD SIDEBURN'S MISSUS.

38
00:03:29,288 --> 00:03:30,955
THIS BLOWS SO HARD.

39
00:03:30,988 --> 00:03:34,922
BON AND KONEKO
ARE IN TAMAGAWA
TO HUNT FOR BARIYONS.

40
00:03:34,955 --> 00:03:38,388
I'M STARTING TO THINK
THOSE GUYS ARE THE ONES
WHO GOT THE BEST DEAL.

41
00:03:38,422 --> 00:03:39,855
[GIRL]
WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO NEXT?
[WHINES]

42
00:03:39,888 --> 00:03:42,922
LET'S SIT BY THE WATER.
OKAY. HURRY UP.

43
00:03:42,955 --> 00:03:46,922
WE'RE NOT GONNA SELL JACK TODAY
UNLESS WE GET A HOT GIRL
TO STAND BY THE GRILL.

44
00:03:46,955 --> 00:03:50,022
HUH?
HOW COME IZUMO'S NOT OUT
HERE SUFFERING WITH US?

45
00:03:50,055 --> 00:03:52,355
LEAST SHE COULD
DO IS SUCK IT UP
FOR AN HOUR.

46
00:03:52,388 --> 00:03:55,555
BUT I GUESS SHE'S NOT
WHAT YOU'D CALL
A TEAM PLAYER, IS SHE?

47
00:03:55,588 --> 00:03:57,055
[KAMIKI]
UH, EXCUSE ME?

48
00:04:00,188 --> 00:04:02,222
[SHOUTS]
OH, HEY.

49
00:04:02,255 --> 00:04:05,022
AH, GEE, YOU LOOK REALLY CUTE
IN THAT SWIMSUIT OF YOURS.

50
00:04:05,055 --> 00:04:08,655
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?
I HELPED YOU GRILL
THOSE SQUIDS, DIDN'T I?

51
00:04:08,688 --> 00:04:11,755
BESIDES, I'M NOT REALLY THE KIND
OF GIRL WHO WORKS RETAIL.

52
00:04:11,788 --> 00:04:14,855
I-I GUESS YOU HAVE A POINT.
HEY, DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

53
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:17,222
I ALREADY WENT SWIMMING,
SO HAVE A BLAST.

54
00:04:17,255 --> 00:04:18,755
OH, DON'T WORRY.
I WILL.

55
00:04:18,788 --> 00:04:21,588
IT'S MY TURN
TO GO SWIMMING ANYWAY.

56
00:04:22,855 --> 00:04:24,655
[BOTH SIGH]
YEP, THAT'S OUR GIRL.

57
00:04:24,688 --> 00:04:27,122
SHE'S ALL <i>TSUN</i>
WITHOUT ANY TRACE OF <i>DERE.</i>

58
00:04:27,155 --> 00:04:29,288
GOOD WORK, BOYS.

59
00:04:29,322 --> 00:04:33,122
I'M TRULY BLESSED TO HAVE
SUCH WONDERFUL STUDENTS
UNDER MY WING.

60
00:04:33,155 --> 00:04:34,755
BY THE WAY,
HOW'S BUSINESS?

61
00:04:34,788 --> 00:04:36,255
[GROANS]

62
00:04:36,288 --> 00:04:38,122
[SEAGULL SQUAWKS]

63
00:04:40,922 --> 00:04:43,922
[THINKING]
I'M NOT A TEAM PLAYER, HUH?

64
00:04:43,955 --> 00:04:45,922
WHATEVER.

65
00:04:45,955 --> 00:04:48,722
THIS FEELS GREAT.

66
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:52,222
I HAVEN'T FELT THIS WAY
IN AGES.

67
00:04:52,255 --> 00:04:55,455
[SIGHS]
I'VE HAD SO MUCH TO DEAL WITH.

68
00:04:55,488 --> 00:04:57,722
[GASPS]
OH, NO! LEG CRAMP!

69
00:04:57,755 --> 00:04:58,922
[GROANING]

70
00:04:58,955 --> 00:05:00,488
HUH?

71
00:05:02,622 --> 00:05:04,422
ARE YOU OKAY?
WHAT'S WRONG?

72
00:05:04,455 --> 00:05:06,055
- [GASPS]
- [SHOUTING]

73
00:05:06,088 --> 00:05:07,722
HEY, QUIT HITTING ME!

74
00:05:09,255 --> 00:05:11,588
[GROANS]

75
00:05:17,188 --> 00:05:18,988
- [GASPS]
- [GROANS]

76
00:05:20,922 --> 00:05:24,555
WHAT THE HELL?
ALL I WAS GONNA DO WAS GIVE YOU
MOUTH-TO-MOUTH RESUSCITATION.

77
00:05:24,588 --> 00:05:27,988
DON'T GIVE ME THAT.
YOU GRABBED MY BOOBS,
YOU BEAT ME.

78
00:05:28,022 --> 00:05:31,388
NOW YOU WANNA KISS ME?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
I JUST SAVED YOUR LIFE.

79
00:05:31,422 --> 00:05:33,222
QUIT BEING
A HARDHEADED JERK.

80
00:05:33,255 --> 00:05:35,588
I'M HARDHEADED?
HOW'D I GET THIS LUMP?

81
00:05:35,622 --> 00:05:38,855
OH, YEAH? WELL, MY CHIN'S
WORSE THAN YOUR--

82
00:05:40,388 --> 00:05:42,755
WHAT?
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?

83
00:05:42,788 --> 00:05:45,855
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE REALLY CUTE.

84
00:05:49,255 --> 00:05:51,588
YEAH. WHAT DO YOU KNOW?
YOU'RE JUST A KID.

85
00:05:51,622 --> 00:05:54,155
I AM NOT A KID.
I'M YOHEI.

86
00:05:54,188 --> 00:05:55,922
[SHIMA]
HEY!

87
00:05:55,955 --> 00:05:59,022
ARE YOU OKAY?
I HOPE YOU KNOW
HOW LUCKY YOU ARE.

88
00:05:59,055 --> 00:06:02,155
HEY, WAIT.
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE GUY
WHO SAVED YOU?

89
00:06:02,188 --> 00:06:04,455
HE LEAVE ALREADY?
I'M RIGHT HERE.

90
00:06:04,488 --> 00:06:07,955
HUH? OH, HEY,
YOU'RE SO SMALL
I DIDN'T SEE YOU.

91
00:06:07,988 --> 00:06:11,355
OH, YEAH? MY DAD SAYS A GUY
CAN BE SMALL AND BE A MAN...

92
00:06:11,388 --> 00:06:13,188
AS LONG AS HE'S BIG
WHERE IT COUNTS!

93
00:06:13,222 --> 00:06:14,722
[GASPS]
DON'T TALK LIKE THAT.

94
00:06:14,755 --> 00:06:18,355
WHY NOT? WHAT,
YOU DON'T LIKE GUYS
WITH BIG HEARTS OR SOMETHING?

95
00:06:18,388 --> 00:06:19,588
UH--

96
00:06:19,622 --> 00:06:21,155
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]

97
00:06:25,322 --> 00:06:28,055
I WONDER WHAT'S GOING ON
UP THERE.

98
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:29,388
HEY, WHERE YOU GOING?

99
00:06:29,422 --> 00:06:31,455
[CHATTERING]

100
00:06:34,588 --> 00:06:36,122
WHOA, WHAT IS THAT?

101
00:06:41,355 --> 00:06:43,488
WHATEVER IT IS
CAN'T BE GOOD.

102
00:06:43,522 --> 00:06:45,155
[MAN]
IT'S A DEMON.

103
00:06:46,822 --> 00:06:49,688
IT'S SAID THAT WHEN THE SEA
TURNS BLACK AS INK,

104
00:06:49,722 --> 00:06:53,088
A DEMON THE SIZE
OF A SMALL MOUNTAIN
SHALL RISE FROM IT...

105
00:06:53,122 --> 00:06:56,155
- AND DESTROY EVERYTHING.
- WHERE'D YOU HEAR THAT?

106
00:06:56,188 --> 00:06:59,488
IT'S A LEGEND THAT'S BEEN PASSED
DOWN FOR GENERATIONS.

107
00:06:59,522 --> 00:07:01,022
MERCY ON US.

108
00:07:01,055 --> 00:07:02,555
[BIRD SINGING]

109
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,422
[RIN]
UH, WHAT IS THAT?

110
00:07:04,455 --> 00:07:05,855
[MAN]
A VOTIVE TABLET.

111
00:07:05,888 --> 00:07:08,788
FOUR HUNDRED YEARS AGO
THIS TEMPLE'S PRIEST MADE IT.

112
00:07:08,822 --> 00:07:11,755
THAT'S A BIG SQUID.
LIKE, REALLY BIG.

113
00:07:11,788 --> 00:07:15,188
THE SEA HAS TURNED
BLACK FROM THE INK
OF THAT MONSTER.

114
00:07:15,222 --> 00:07:17,888
YEAH, BUT THAT'S JUST A STORY,
ISN'T IT?

115
00:07:17,922 --> 00:07:21,922
I WISH IT WERE.
WE EXPERIENCED THIS
SIX MONTHS AGO.

116
00:07:21,955 --> 00:07:24,288
THE SEA TURNED BLACK
JUST LIKE TODAY,

117
00:07:24,322 --> 00:07:28,922
AND A FISHERMAN
SET OUT IN HIS BOAT
TO DRIVE AWAY THE DEMON.

118
00:07:28,955 --> 00:07:33,688
HOWEVER, TO THIS DAY,
THAT MAN HAS NOT RETURNED.

119
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,426
JUST OUR LUCK.

120
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,498
I DIDN'T THINK
WE'D BE HEARING ABOUT DEMONS
THIS FAR FROM SCHOOL.

121
00:07:43,531 --> 00:07:47,665
DON'T YOU THINK IT'D BE COOL
IF OUR VERY FIRST MISSION
WAS TO GO AND KILL THAT DEMON?

122
00:07:47,698 --> 00:07:49,298
[GRUNTS]
WHAT THE HELL?
[MEOWS]

123
00:07:49,331 --> 00:07:50,598
OW!

124
00:07:50,631 --> 00:07:52,198
WATCH WHERE YOU'RE GOING.

125
00:07:52,231 --> 00:07:53,965
LOOK,
OUR LITTLE FRIEND'S BACK.

126
00:07:53,998 --> 00:07:55,765
YOU KNOW,
WE WERE WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

127
00:07:55,798 --> 00:07:57,365
WHERE'D YOU DISAPPEAR TO?

128
00:07:57,398 --> 00:07:59,765
HMM! NOWHERE.
NOWHERE, HUH?

129
00:07:59,798 --> 00:08:02,431
MAN, YOU ARE
ONE HARDHEADED KID.

130
00:08:02,465 --> 00:08:04,031
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

131
00:08:04,065 --> 00:08:07,665
- DOES YOUR HEAD STILL HURT?
- YEAH. OF COURSE IT DOES.

132
00:08:08,865 --> 00:08:11,231
- SORRY ABOUT THAT.
- [GASPS]

133
00:08:11,265 --> 00:08:15,165
COME ON, KID. YOU HAD TO SEE US
COMING YOUR WAY, DIDN'T YOU?

134
00:08:15,198 --> 00:08:17,831
YOU COULD'VE JUST GIVEN US
A LITTLE ROOM TO GET BY.

135
00:08:17,865 --> 00:08:21,265
NO WAY. MY DAD TOLD ME
THAT A REAL MAN WALKS
A STRAIGHT PATH,

136
00:08:21,298 --> 00:08:22,665
AND THAT'S ALL I WAS DOING.

137
00:08:22,698 --> 00:08:25,165
I THINK YOUR OLD MAN
MEANT THAT METAPHORICALLY.

138
00:08:25,198 --> 00:08:26,665
AND BESIDES,
IF YOU ONLY GO STRAIGHT,

139
00:08:26,698 --> 00:08:28,798
I'M PRETTY SURE
YOU'RE GONNA WIND UP LOST.

140
00:08:28,831 --> 00:08:31,698
NO ONE'S THAT DUMB.
DO ANY OF YOU KNOW
HOW TO GET TO THE PET STORE?

141
00:08:31,731 --> 00:08:33,931
- [BOTH] HUH?
- I NEED TO GET
TO THE PET STORE.

142
00:08:33,965 --> 00:08:36,131
I DREW A MAP OF IT,
BUT I CAN'T FIND IT.

143
00:08:36,165 --> 00:08:37,965
HMM.
YEAH.

144
00:08:37,998 --> 00:08:40,665
YEAH, WHAT?
YOU GOT A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

145
00:08:41,831 --> 00:08:43,665
[KAMIKI]
IT STILL BLOWS MY MIND...

146
00:08:43,698 --> 00:08:46,698
THAT WE HAD TO GIVE DIRECTIONS
TO ONE OF THE LOCALS.

147
00:08:46,731 --> 00:08:49,031
SHE'S RIGHT.
HAVEN'T YOU EVER
BEEN HERE BEFORE?

148
00:08:49,065 --> 00:08:50,665
YEAH, BUT MY DOG'S SICK.

149
00:08:50,698 --> 00:08:53,531
YOUR DOG?
SO WHENEVER YOU NEED
TO GO TO THE PET STORE,

150
00:08:53,565 --> 00:08:55,365
YOUR DOG'S THE ONE
THAT TAKES YOU THERE?

151
00:08:55,398 --> 00:08:56,998
YEAH.
SO WHAT?
I KNEW IT.

152
00:08:57,031 --> 00:08:59,598
YOU'RE SEVERELY
DIRECTIONALLY CHALLENGED.

153
00:08:59,631 --> 00:09:02,465
I DON'T WANNA BRAG, BUT MY DAD'S
ON A WHOLE 'NOTHER LEVEL.

154
00:09:02,498 --> 00:09:05,065
HE WAS, LIKE, TOTALLY
DIRECTIONALLY CHALLENGED.

155
00:09:05,098 --> 00:09:07,098
I WOULDN'T BRAG
ABOUT THAT.

156
00:09:07,131 --> 00:09:10,098
ANYWAY, WHY DOES EVERY TOPIC
REVERT BACK TO YOUR DAD?

157
00:09:10,131 --> 00:09:12,298
'CAUSE HE WAS PRETTY AWESOME.

158
00:09:12,331 --> 00:09:15,098
YOU MEAN, HE'S--

159
00:09:15,131 --> 00:09:18,565
SIX MONTHS AGO HE SHIPPED OUT
TO KILL THAT THING,
BUT HE DIDN'T COME BACK.

160
00:09:18,598 --> 00:09:20,465
WAIT.
YOUR DAD WAS THAT GUY?

161
00:09:20,498 --> 00:09:23,498
AND THAT THING
HE WAS AFTER WAS--

162
00:09:23,531 --> 00:09:28,065
THE DEMON OF THE DEEP SEAS.
THAT'S WHAT THEY CALL THE THING
THAT KILLED MY DAD.

163
00:09:28,098 --> 00:09:33,798
I SWORE THAT NO MATTER WHAT,
I'D FIND IT AND KILL IT.

164
00:09:33,831 --> 00:09:35,131
[GASPS]

165
00:09:36,798 --> 00:09:39,331
[TSUBAKI]
THANKS FOR ALL THE HARD WORK.
DIG IN.

166
00:09:39,365 --> 00:09:42,698
[SHIMA]
SQUID SASHIMI, SQUID NOODLES
SWEET-AND-SOUR SQUID.

167
00:09:42,731 --> 00:09:45,365
[KAMIKI]
SQUID AND NATTO,
SQUID INK SPAGHETTI?

168
00:09:45,398 --> 00:09:48,131
[GROANS]
EVERYTHING HERE'S
GOT SQUID IN IT.

169
00:09:48,165 --> 00:09:49,765
THAT'S RIGHT.
BON APPÉTIT.

170
00:09:49,798 --> 00:09:53,265
YEAH, BUT IT'S LIKE,
DON'T WE HAVE ANYTHING
BESIDES SQUID?

171
00:09:53,298 --> 00:09:55,498
NO, WE DON'T.
DO YOU KNOW WHY?

172
00:09:55,531 --> 00:09:59,065
NO ONE HAS BEEN ABLE TO CATCH
ANYTHING IN THESE WATERS
EXCEPT SQUID.

173
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:01,798
- IT'S DRIVING
EVERYONE SQUIDLY.
- [BOTH GROAN]

174
00:10:01,831 --> 00:10:05,098
HOWEVER, ON THE UPSIDE,
YOU CAN ALL SQUID OUT
TILL YOU GET SICK.

175
00:10:05,131 --> 00:10:06,498
[CHUCKLES]

176
00:10:06,531 --> 00:10:10,665
THAT'S WHY NO ONE
BOUGHT OUR SQUID.
IT FIGURES.

177
00:10:10,698 --> 00:10:12,698
- [RIN]
A KRAKEN?
- IF WE'RE TALKING...

178
00:10:12,731 --> 00:10:15,965
ABOUT INK-SPEWING DEMONS
OF THE SEA,
THAT'S MY GUESS.

179
00:10:15,998 --> 00:10:18,731
THIS BOOK,
THE NATURAL HISTORY OF NORWAY,

180
00:10:18,765 --> 00:10:21,365
HAS A PASSAGE THAT TELLS
HOW IF A KRAKEN'S AROUND,

181
00:10:21,398 --> 00:10:23,865
THE SEA WILL TURN PITCH BLACK
FROM ITS INK.

182
00:10:23,898 --> 00:10:25,398
[SHIMA]
SO THAT THING'S
THE REASON...

183
00:10:25,431 --> 00:10:27,298
WHY FISHERMAN CAN'T CATCH
ANYTHING BUT SQUID.

184
00:10:27,331 --> 00:10:32,798
OKAY, WE FIGURED OUT A KRAKEN'S
DOING THIS, BUT IS THERE
ANY WAY TO DESTROY IT?

185
00:10:32,831 --> 00:10:36,198
ONE WOULD HAVE TO KNOW THE DEMON
OF THE DEEP SEA'S FATAL VERSE.

186
00:10:36,231 --> 00:10:40,598
IT'S BELIEVED TO BE THE LETTER
TO THE EPHESIANS 1:18.

187
00:10:41,965 --> 00:10:44,631
OTHER THAN THAT,
THE OPTIONS ARE LIMITED.

188
00:10:44,665 --> 00:10:47,465
I'M AFRAID
YOUR LITTLE FRIEND CAN'T
DESTROY IT BY HIMSELF.

189
00:10:47,498 --> 00:10:52,131
- [GASPS]
- [CELL PHONE RINGING]

190
00:10:52,165 --> 00:10:53,631
[GASPS]

191
00:10:53,665 --> 00:10:56,631
WHAT IS IT, HONEY?
WHAT? AGAIN?

192
00:10:56,665 --> 00:10:58,865
DON'T WORRY, KITTY CAT.
I'M ON MY WAY.

193
00:10:58,898 --> 00:11:02,831
UH, YEAH.
SOMETHING JUST CAME UP,
SO I HAVE TO GO FOR A BIT.

194
00:11:02,865 --> 00:11:04,898
YOU CAN TAKE
THE DAY OFF TOMORROW.

195
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:07,998
WE'VE HIRED A PROPER
EMPLOYEE TO WORK PART
TIME AT THE OCEAN HOUSE.

196
00:11:08,031 --> 00:11:11,265
WHAT'S HE MEAN,
PROPER EMPLOYEE?
WHAT ARE WE, INTERNS?

197
00:11:11,298 --> 00:11:14,098
WHO CARES ABOUT THAT?
I WANNA KNOW WHO
KITTY CAT IS.

198
00:11:14,131 --> 00:11:17,765
HUH. OKUMURA, YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS MEANS?
WHAT?

199
00:11:17,798 --> 00:11:20,098
WE'RE GONNA SWIM
OUR ASSES OFF.

200
00:11:20,131 --> 00:11:21,731
RIGHT ON!
WHAT THE--

201
00:11:21,765 --> 00:11:23,731
I'M SORRY,
I FORGOT TO TELL YOU.

202
00:11:23,765 --> 00:11:27,831
I WANT YOU TO MAKE SURE
THAT YOHEI BOY DOESN'T GET
ANYWHERE NEAR THAT DEMON.

203
00:11:27,865 --> 00:11:30,465
THAT'S RIGHT,
YOU'RE BABY-SITTING TOMORROW.
BYE-BYE.

204
00:11:30,498 --> 00:11:33,531
[BOTH GROAN]

205
00:11:39,765 --> 00:11:42,398
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE REALLY CUTE.

206
00:11:42,431 --> 00:11:44,098
[SIGHS]

207
00:11:45,598 --> 00:11:47,865
[THINKING]
WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?

208
00:11:50,631 --> 00:11:53,398
IT'S YOU.
HEY, WHAT'S UP?

209
00:11:53,431 --> 00:11:55,798
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

210
00:11:58,031 --> 00:11:59,065
HERE.

211
00:12:00,365 --> 00:12:03,531
- WHAT IS IT?
- IT'S AN OINTMENT.

212
00:12:03,565 --> 00:12:06,931
MY DAD ALWAYS TOOK IT WITH HIM
WHEN HE WENT OUT TO SEA.

213
00:12:06,965 --> 00:12:09,465
PUT SOME ON YOUR HEAD.
IT REALLY WORKS.

214
00:12:09,498 --> 00:12:12,998
- YOU CAME HERE
TO GIVE ME THIS?
- [LAUGHS]

215
00:12:21,465 --> 00:12:23,698
HEY!
[GASPS]

216
00:12:23,731 --> 00:12:28,531
SORRY.
I'M SORTA LOST HERE.
HOW DO I GET HOME?

217
00:12:39,517 --> 00:12:41,950
[SNORING]

218
00:12:43,555 --> 00:12:47,088
[KURO] WAKE UP, RIN.
IT'S THE SEA AGAIN.
IT'S SERIOUS.

219
00:12:47,122 --> 00:12:48,955
HUH?

220
00:12:51,522 --> 00:12:53,222
NOT AGAIN.

221
00:12:53,255 --> 00:12:55,788
I'M SURE THAT KID'S
SEEING THIS TOO.

222
00:12:55,822 --> 00:12:58,655
I JUST HOPE HE DOESN'T DO
ANYTHING STUPID.

223
00:12:58,688 --> 00:13:00,755
I'M GONNA GO CHECK ON HIM.
IZUMO?

224
00:13:00,788 --> 00:13:04,622
YEAH, WHAT?
HE SAVED MY LIFE, DIDN'T HE?

225
00:13:04,655 --> 00:13:09,755
ANYWAY, IT BUGS ME
WHEN PEOPLE GO OFF AND DO
SOMETHING HALF-COCKED.

226
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:11,655
[PANTING]

227
00:13:33,088 --> 00:13:35,222
SHE SAYS WE DON'T NEED
TO COME OUT THERE YET.

228
00:13:35,255 --> 00:13:37,788
SHE'S GOTTA BE HUNGRY
BY NOW.

229
00:13:37,822 --> 00:13:39,388
DON'T YOU THINK
IT'S KINDA WEIRD?

230
00:13:39,422 --> 00:13:42,422
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE HER
TO GET SO WORRIED
ABOUT SOMEONE ELSE.

231
00:13:42,455 --> 00:13:43,388
HMM.

232
00:13:45,955 --> 00:13:50,688
[KAMIKI]
HEY, ARE YOU GONNA SIT THERE
AND KEEP WATCHING ALL NIGHT?

233
00:13:50,722 --> 00:13:53,755
I'M GONNA WAIT
AS LONG AS IT TAKES...

234
00:13:53,788 --> 00:13:55,855
UNTIL THAT THING
SHOWS UP.

235
00:13:55,888 --> 00:14:00,055
BUT IF IT REALLY IS A DEMON OUT
THERE, THEN THERE'S NO WAY YOU
CAN KILL IT ALL BY YOURSELF.

236
00:14:00,088 --> 00:14:01,688
BUTT OUT, WILL YA?

237
00:14:01,722 --> 00:14:03,655
IT KILLED MY DAD, DIDN'T IT?

238
00:14:03,688 --> 00:14:07,355
IF IT'S THE LAST THING I DO,
I'M GONNA KILL THAT DAMN THING.

239
00:14:09,488 --> 00:14:12,922
[SIGHS]
YOU'RE REALLY SOMETHING,
YOU KNOW THAT?

240
00:14:12,955 --> 00:14:16,855
LISTEN, HAVE YOU EVEN THOUGHT
THIS THROUGH?

241
00:14:16,888 --> 00:14:20,988
'CAUSE NO MATTER HOW BAD
YOU WANNA DO SOMETHING,
SOME THINGS JUST CAN'T BE DONE.

242
00:14:21,022 --> 00:14:24,222
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
I'M SAYING THIS, BUT--

243
00:14:24,255 --> 00:14:27,388
BUT YOU'RE BEING STUPID,
AND YOU'RE GONNA GET BURNED.

244
00:14:27,422 --> 00:14:31,088
SO? WHEN YOU'RE ABOUT
TO GET BURNED, WHAT?
DO YOU RUN AWAY?

245
00:14:31,122 --> 00:14:34,388
- [GASPS]
- KNOW WHAT MY DAD SAID?

246
00:14:34,422 --> 00:14:37,088
HE SAID THAT PEOPLE
ONLY SAY NEGATIVE THINGS...

247
00:14:37,122 --> 00:14:39,588
WHEN THEY DON'T HAVE
ANY CONFIDENCE IN THEMSELVES.

248
00:14:39,622 --> 00:14:41,888
THAT JUST BECAUSE
THEY'RE SCARED OR CONFUSED,

249
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:44,455
THEY WANT EVERYONE ELSE
TO FEEL LIKE THEY DO.

250
00:14:44,488 --> 00:14:47,655
WHY, YOU-- WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

251
00:14:47,688 --> 00:14:52,455
LISTEN, YOU.
FOR YOUR INFORMATION,
I'VE GOT A TON OF CONFIDENCE.

252
00:14:52,488 --> 00:14:54,388
THEN WHAT
DO YOU CARE?

253
00:14:54,422 --> 00:14:57,355
IT DOESN'T MATTER
IF YOU LOSE YOUR WAY.

254
00:14:57,388 --> 00:15:00,188
THING IS, YOU CAN'T CHICKEN OUT
ONCE YOU'VE MADE UP YOUR MIND.

255
00:15:00,222 --> 00:15:01,888
[GASPS]

256
00:15:01,922 --> 00:15:04,388
THAT'S ANOTHER THING
MY DAD ALWAYS SAID.

257
00:15:04,422 --> 00:15:08,888
AND I KNOW WHEN HE FOUND
THAT DEMON, MY DAD MADE UP
HIS MIND AND DIDN'T HESITATE.

258
00:15:08,922 --> 00:15:11,622
I'M NOT GONNA
HESITATE EITHER.

259
00:15:11,655 --> 00:15:14,622
- I'M GONNA TAKE THAT DEMON ON,
JUST LIKE HE--
- [SPLASHING]

260
00:15:14,655 --> 00:15:15,888
[GASPING]

261
00:15:15,922 --> 00:15:17,655
THERE IT IS!

262
00:15:18,755 --> 00:15:21,155
[SCREECHING]

263
00:15:21,188 --> 00:15:23,688
THAT'S HIM,
ALL RIGHT.

264
00:15:23,722 --> 00:15:26,388
[GASPS]
WAIT, YOHEI!

265
00:15:27,488 --> 00:15:30,722
- NO WAY!
- IT-IT REALLY IS A DEMON.

266
00:15:30,755 --> 00:15:32,588
WHERE'S CAPTAIN NEMO
WHEN YOU NEED HIM?

267
00:15:32,622 --> 00:15:34,155
WHATEVER.
JUST READ THE SUTRA.

268
00:15:34,188 --> 00:15:36,055
IT'S NOT A SUTRA.
IT'S AN ARIA.

269
00:15:36,088 --> 00:15:37,855
WHOA, WAIT.
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

270
00:15:37,888 --> 00:15:39,455
I HAVEN'T FIGURED
THAT OUT YET.

271
00:15:39,488 --> 00:15:42,055
BUT WE HAVE TO STOP IT
OR IT'LL DESTROY THE VILLAGE.

272
00:15:42,088 --> 00:15:43,922
BESIDES,
THERE'S THAT KID.

273
00:15:43,955 --> 00:15:46,122
HE COULD GET HURT
IF HE TRIES ANYTHING.

274
00:15:46,155 --> 00:15:48,422
[SIGHS]
RIGHT. HERE GOES NOTHING.

275
00:15:48,455 --> 00:15:51,322
"THEN WITH THE EYES
OF YOUR HEARTS ENLIGHTENED,

276
00:15:51,355 --> 00:15:53,855
YOU WILL KNOW THE HOPE
TO WHICH HE HAS CALLED YOU.

277
00:15:53,888 --> 00:15:58,222
THE GLORY THAT IS
HIS INHERITANCE AMONG THE SAINTS
OF THE UNLIMITED GREATNESS...

278
00:15:58,255 --> 00:16:01,555
OF-- OF HIS POWER
FOR US WHO BELIEVE."

279
00:16:01,588 --> 00:16:05,788
IT'S NOT WORKING.
YOU THINK MAYBE IT'S 'CAUSE
SQUIDS CAN'T HEAR?

280
00:16:05,822 --> 00:16:10,188
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
CAN'T YOU SEE THAT THING'S GOT
GINORMOUS EARS?

281
00:16:12,222 --> 00:16:16,355
SERIOUSLY? YOU KNOW,
THOSE THINGS AREN'T EARS.
THEY'RE FINS, MAN!

282
00:16:16,388 --> 00:16:18,522
THEY ARE? REALLY?

283
00:16:18,555 --> 00:16:20,388
[SHRIEKING]

284
00:16:20,422 --> 00:16:22,455
[SHOUTING]

285
00:16:30,855 --> 00:16:32,522
- [SCREECHING]
- KURO!

286
00:16:36,655 --> 00:16:39,088
- [SNARLING]
- [ROARING]

287
00:16:43,955 --> 00:16:47,355
WHOA. THIS IS LIKE
A MONSTER MOVIE.

288
00:16:47,388 --> 00:16:49,322
KICK HIS ASS, KURO!

289
00:16:49,355 --> 00:16:50,355
[SNARLING]

290
00:17:00,722 --> 00:17:02,922
ATTABOY, KURO!
NOT GOOD.

291
00:17:02,955 --> 00:17:05,022
WHY NOT?
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT EITHER?

292
00:17:05,055 --> 00:17:07,555
THE THING
ABOUT CATS IS--
[SHOUTS]

293
00:17:11,188 --> 00:17:12,488
KURO!

294
00:17:12,522 --> 00:17:13,555
[WEAKLY]
RIN.

295
00:17:13,588 --> 00:17:15,455
KURO, ARE YOU OKAY?

296
00:17:15,488 --> 00:17:16,888
I'M DIZZY.

297
00:17:16,922 --> 00:17:19,722
CATS CAN'T EAT RAW SQUID.
IT PARALYZES THEM.

298
00:17:19,755 --> 00:17:21,422
FOR REAL?
[KAMIKI]
WHERE'S YOHEI?

299
00:17:21,455 --> 00:17:24,488
DID HE COME THIS WAY?
NO. WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE HE IS.

300
00:17:24,522 --> 00:17:26,622
REALLY?
OH, NO.

301
00:17:26,655 --> 00:17:28,855
DON'T TELL ME
HE GOT LOST AGAIN.

302
00:17:28,888 --> 00:17:30,822
[ROARING]

303
00:17:30,855 --> 00:17:33,455
THAT SETTLES IT.
IT'S UP TO ME.
HEY!

304
00:17:35,055 --> 00:17:37,622
I HUMBLY APPEAL TO THEE,
OH, GODDESS INARI.

305
00:17:37,655 --> 00:17:39,222
[SHIMA]
WATCH OUT, IZUMO!

306
00:17:45,622 --> 00:17:47,655
I CAN'T SUMMON THEM.

307
00:17:53,655 --> 00:17:55,388
[BLUBBERING]

308
00:17:55,955 --> 00:17:57,722
[SHRIEKING]

309
00:17:57,755 --> 00:17:59,355
[ALL GASPING]

310
00:18:05,455 --> 00:18:08,488
- I'M GONNA KILL THAT THING.
- IT'S YOHEI.

311
00:18:08,522 --> 00:18:10,355
WAIT.
WHERE'S HE GOING?

312
00:18:11,755 --> 00:18:13,422
STUPID KID.

313
00:18:17,022 --> 00:18:18,388
[SHRIEKING]

314
00:18:21,522 --> 00:18:24,122
[RIN]
YOU'RE IN WAY OVER YOUR HEAD.
GET AWAY.

315
00:18:24,155 --> 00:18:26,222
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU'RE JUST A KID...

316
00:18:26,255 --> 00:18:28,222
AND THAT DEMON'S
NOT MESSING AROUND.

317
00:18:28,255 --> 00:18:30,188
SHUT UP
AND STAY OUT OF MY WAY!

318
00:18:30,222 --> 00:18:32,055
I'M GONNA KILL
THAT ROTTEN DEMON,

319
00:18:32,088 --> 00:18:34,122
AND I'M GONNA GET REVENGE
FOR MY DAD.

320
00:18:34,155 --> 00:18:35,122
HEY!

321
00:18:39,422 --> 00:18:41,255
[SHRIEKING]

322
00:18:41,288 --> 00:18:42,655
I DID IT!

323
00:18:45,655 --> 00:18:47,122
[SHOUTING]

324
00:18:48,755 --> 00:18:50,255
OH, CRAP!

325
00:18:51,522 --> 00:18:52,522
[BOTH GASP]

326
00:19:00,988 --> 00:19:03,588
DAMN IT.
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

327
00:19:10,855 --> 00:19:13,122
[SHOUTING]
[MAN]
AHOY!

328
00:19:13,155 --> 00:19:14,755
AHOY!

329
00:19:14,788 --> 00:19:17,822
YOHEI! AHOY!

330
00:19:17,855 --> 00:19:20,422
YOHEI!

331
00:19:20,455 --> 00:19:22,055
YOHEI!

332
00:19:22,088 --> 00:19:23,722
WHA-- WHO'S THAT GUY?

333
00:19:23,755 --> 00:19:25,022
YOHEI!
[GASPS]

334
00:19:25,055 --> 00:19:27,888
- THAT SOUNDS LIKE--
- YOHEI!

335
00:19:27,922 --> 00:19:29,722
IT'S DAD!
HUH?

336
00:19:29,755 --> 00:19:31,622
IT'S-- IT'S DAD!

337
00:19:31,655 --> 00:19:33,155
WHAT THE--

338
00:19:33,188 --> 00:19:35,388
[YOHEI]
AHOY, DAD!

339
00:19:39,588 --> 00:19:41,655
GOOD WORK, EVERYONE.

340
00:19:41,688 --> 00:19:45,122
BY THE WAY, SIDEBURN--
UM, MR. TSUBAKI--
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

341
00:19:45,155 --> 00:19:47,855
WELL, I WASN'T SURE
IF IT WAS A KRAKEN.

342
00:19:47,888 --> 00:19:52,288
BUT IF IT TURNED OUT IT WAS,
I KNEW WE NEEDED A PROPER
STRATEGY TO FIGHT IT.

343
00:19:52,322 --> 00:19:54,955
THEN I DISCOVERED
THAT THERE WASN'T
ANY REAL DANGER.

344
00:19:54,988 --> 00:19:57,855
[FATHER]
I TRIED, BUT I COULDN'T
FIGURE OUT HOW TO GET BACK.

345
00:19:57,888 --> 00:20:02,788
I MADE IT TO A DESERTED ISLAND
AND STAYED THERE FOR A BIT,
THEN STRUCK OUT TO SEA AGAIN.

346
00:20:02,822 --> 00:20:06,255
I FLOATED AROUND
AND TRIED TO FIND JAPAN
WITH THE HELP OF THAT SQUID,

347
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:08,222
BUT THAT THING'S GOT
NO SENSE OF DIRECTION.

348
00:20:08,255 --> 00:20:10,588
BUT I THOUGHT
THAT SQUID
WAS YOUR ENEMY.

349
00:20:10,622 --> 00:20:13,888
YOHEI, MY BOY,
YOU NEED TO LEARN
TO BE MORE FLEXIBLE.

350
00:20:13,922 --> 00:20:17,255
- HUH?
- THAT'S WHAT I REALIZED
DURING OUR BATTLE.

351
00:20:17,288 --> 00:20:21,355
BE LIKE THE SQUID.
HE'S FLEXIBLE IN MIND,
BODY AND SOUL.

352
00:20:21,388 --> 00:20:24,855
HE TURNED OVER A NEW LEAF,
SO WHY CAN'T WE ALL?

353
00:20:24,888 --> 00:20:27,055
BUT YOU SAID ONCE A MAN
DECIDES TO DO SOMETHING,

354
00:20:27,088 --> 00:20:28,588
HE'S GOTTA FOLLOW THROUGH
WITH IT.

355
00:20:28,622 --> 00:20:32,255
YOHEI! ENOUGH.
BE LIKE THE FLAVOR
OF SQUID SASHIMI.

356
00:20:32,288 --> 00:20:34,288
WHAT THE HELL
DOES THAT MEAN?

357
00:20:34,322 --> 00:20:37,155
A MAN ALSO HAS TO HAVE
THE COURAGE TO CHANGE HIS MIND.

358
00:20:37,188 --> 00:20:39,088
THAT'S WHAT BEING A MAN'S
ALL ABOUT.

359
00:20:39,122 --> 00:20:40,655
[YOHEI]
UH, OKAY.

360
00:20:40,688 --> 00:20:43,688
YOU KNOW, I THINK
I'M WAY MORE MATURE NOW
BECAUSE OF THIS.

361
00:20:43,722 --> 00:20:44,822
OH, GOD.

362
00:20:44,855 --> 00:20:48,222
[GRUNTS]
COME HERE, YOHEI!

363
00:20:48,255 --> 00:20:49,855
DAD!

364
00:20:49,888 --> 00:20:53,355
[SNIFFLING]
THAT'S SO AWESOME.

365
00:20:53,388 --> 00:20:54,822
SERIOUSLY?

366
00:20:54,855 --> 00:20:57,288
EVEN DEMONS CAN HAVE
A CHANGE OF HEART.

367
00:20:57,322 --> 00:20:59,388
THAT'S WHAT I WAS TRYING
TO TEACH YOU.

368
00:20:59,422 --> 00:21:02,455
AND IF ANYTHING,
THAT ALONE MADE THE TRIP
OUT HERE WORTH IT.

369
00:21:02,488 --> 00:21:04,322
THAT'S TOTAL B.S.

370
00:21:04,355 --> 00:21:05,955
[GROANS]

371
00:21:05,988 --> 00:21:10,155
GEEZ! THIS SUCKS!

372
00:21:15,622 --> 00:21:18,455
♪ [MAN SINGING IN JAPANESE]

373
00:22:48,588 --> 00:22:49,988
HUH?

374
00:22:51,788 --> 00:22:53,988
HEY, IT'S THAT KID.

375
00:22:57,722 --> 00:22:59,688
COME TO SAY GOOD-BYE?
MM-HMM.

376
00:22:59,722 --> 00:23:01,555
IS YOUR DOG
FEELING BETTER?

377
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:04,122
YEAH. THIS IS SHIRO.

378
00:23:04,155 --> 00:23:06,222
LOOK AT HIS EYEBROWS.
AREN'T THEY CUTE?

379
00:23:06,255 --> 00:23:07,655
EYEBROWS?

380
00:23:07,688 --> 00:23:09,355
UH-HUH.
THAT'S WHAT I SAID.

381
00:23:11,555 --> 00:23:13,055
[SCREAMING]

382
00:23:13,088 --> 00:23:14,955
[JET ENGINE ROARS]

383
00:23:18,922 --> 00:23:21,088
[HOWLING]

384
00:23:29,988 --> 00:23:31,455
[GIGGLES]
[BOTH GASP]

385
00:23:31,488 --> 00:23:33,288
YEAH, WHAT?

386
00:23:33,322 --> 00:23:36,555
OH, NOTHING.
JUST WONDERING
WHAT'S SO FUNNY IS ALL.

387
00:23:36,588 --> 00:23:38,355
WHAT ELSE CAN I DO
BUT LAUGH?

388
00:23:38,388 --> 00:23:40,788
THIS TRIP WAS
THE MOST RIDICULOUS
THING EVER.

389
00:23:40,822 --> 00:23:42,288
HMM!
YEAH.

390
00:23:42,322 --> 00:23:44,555
I GUESS YOU HAVE
A POINT THERE.

391
00:23:44,588 --> 00:23:45,988
[LAUGHING]

392
00:23:46,022 --> 00:23:48,955
TOTALLY... RIDICULOUS.

393
00:23:51,655 --> 00:23:52,822
WHATEVER.

394
00:23:52,855 --> 00:23:54,688
THIS FEELS GREAT.

395
00:24:02,855 --> 00:24:04,355
[AMAIMON]
AN AMUSEMENT PARK?

396
00:24:04,388 --> 00:24:07,322
[MEPHISTO]
YOU'RE FINALLY IN THE MOOD
TO PLAY WITH HIM.

397
00:24:07,355 --> 00:24:10,255
[SHIMA]
OOH, WOW.
YOU SURE LOOK CUTE, MORIYAMA.

398
00:24:10,288 --> 00:24:14,122
[RIN] AM I SEEING THINGS,
OR IS HER SKIRT, LIKE,
WAY, WAY TOO SHORT?

